'''微觀尺度'''（microscopic scale）指的是[[物體|物體]]或事件的[[尺度|尺度]]小於能夠被[[肉眼|肉眼]]觀看的尺度，因此需要使用[[放大鏡|放大鏡]]或[[顯微鏡|顯微鏡]]來進行清楚的[[觀察|觀察]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=The microscopic scale|url=http://sciencelearn.org.nz/Contexts/Exploring-with-Microscopes/Science-Ideas-and-Concepts/The-microscopic-scale|website=Science Learning Hub|publisher=The University of Waikato|accessdate=31 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420102701/http://sciencelearn.org.nz/Contexts/Exploring-with-Microscopes/Science-Ideas-and-Concepts/The-microscopic-scale|archive-date=2016-04-20|dead-url=yes}}</ref>在[[物理學|物理學]]裡，微觀系統的尺度大約為[[原子|原子]]尺度或小於原子尺度（大約10[[Å|Å]]尺度）。<ref>{{cite book|last=Reif|first=F.|title=Fundamentals of Statistical and Thermal Physics|url=https://archive.org/details/fundamentalsofst00fred|year=1965|publisher=McGraw-Hill|location=Boston|isbn=007-051800-9|edition=International student edition.|page=[https://archive.org/details/fundamentalsofst00fred/page/2 2]|quote=We shall call a system "''micro''scopic (i.e., "''small'' scale) if it is roughly of atomic dimensions or smaller (say of the order of 10 Å or less).}}</ref>[[量子力學|量子力學]]所研究的就是微觀世界的物理[[行為|行為]]。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Jaeger|first1=Gregg|title=What in the (quantum) world is macroscopic?|journal=American Journal of Physics|date=September 2014|volume=82|issue=9|pages=896–905|doi=10.1119/1.4878358|bibcode = 2014AmJPh..82..896J }}</ref>

